I understand benefits of code sharing, but the problems with `s3upDocker` are:
- It is impossible to know (from reading the code) where the artifacts will end up. There is literally no S3 url in its parameters;
- It alters the paths of the files that it receives, splitting them into sub-directories. This is problematic because the index.html file needs to end up at the exact path, while other artifacts should be at some paths that are known beforehand;
- The function has neither documentation nor source code (at least GitHub cannot locate the source code: https://github.com/search?q=s3updocker&type=Code). It might be the permission issue.

