Makes sense! This was speculative suggestion hoping to get something else:
I want to avoid repetition of publish calls between language-specific cases and "all".
I don't want to risk having a language handled in the specific case, but not in "all", or if a language ends up with more complex logic, I want us to avoid having to duplicate that.

If the signatures don't yet match, we can still get this through a different means.
What do you think about something like the following?

```go
func publish(..., lang string) error {
  enabled := func(l string) bool {
    return lang == l || lang == "all"
  }

  if enabled("nodejs") {
    if err := publishNPM(...); err != nil {
      // ...
    }
  }
  if enabled("python") {
    publishPython(..)
  }
```

It's not the cleanest, but it'll meet this goal while leaving flexibility in function signature.

